==English==

{{rank|short|able|five|393|need|met|boy|c.}}

===Etymology===
Old English [[neodian]] (rare); Old English [[nyd|nȳd]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ni:d/

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|need||}}

# {{transitive}}: To have an absolute requirement for.
#:''Living things '''need''' water to survive.''
# {{transitive}}: To want strongly; to feel that one must have something.
#:''After ten days of hiking, I '''needed''' a shower and a shave.''
# (''[[modal verb]]'') To be obliged or required to.
#:''You '''need''' not go if you don't want to.''

====Usage notes====
*As a modal verb, '''need''' does not vary in the [[third person]] when used in the negative (''he need not do it'').<!--is this a subjunctive?-->

